release_note: Custom fonts! Yes now you can install custom fonts from font files! Easy access to hundreds of fonts in Google s free font library. Select font style like bold italic etc. You can now easily change permission to your photos from inside the app. Other enhancements and bug fixes. If you like editing with Superimpose X please consider leaving a review or a rating in the App Store. That really motivates us to keep improving the app.

You can now export your project as PSD file preserving all the layers. You can also share your projects through iCloud AirDrop DropBox email or any other cloud service that you use. Masks can now be exported via iCloud AirDrop email and other cloud services. Improved elliptic and rectangular masks. You can now single tap to switch between rotate and normal mode. An option to rotate orthogonally in rotate mode. Bug fixes.

A new Lens Blur tool. You can now rotate and add gradient to rectangular and elliptic masking tools. A new option in settings to enable tap indicators so that you could use it to create video tutorials. Bugs fixed.

Added a new option called Resize Base . Using this you can change the base size of a project the size at which the final image is exported. Now you can crop an individual layer in the crop tool section. The new Crop Layer tool has an option to automatically crop a layer to the bounding box of the unmasked area. In this update you can find the first set of 5 tutorial videos under the information section. Hope you will like them. Besides that we have fixed a couple of bugs and added a new tool under Editor Tools Mask Outline to create an outline on the mask. Thanks for using Superimpose X! If you like the app please rate or review us on the App Store. We have made number of improvements in this update... An option to match the colors of one layer to that of another. Find this option by tapping the active layer in the Layer Stack. Shrink or expand a mask. Find this under Mask Blur Shrink. This comes very handy to remove the unwanted outlines around a masked object. You can now duplicate a project. It is now easier to delete a project. 8 layers support extend to iPad too iPad Pro and above . Better ordering of the photo albums. Favorite album is now just next to the Camera Roll . So now you do not need to keep looking for it. A new mask viewing mode B W. You can now view the mask in black and white too. Regular brush and Smart Brush now shares the same brush size. Bug fixes.
Fixed a critical bug where the magnifier used to get stuck while using the new color picker tool. If you like using Superimpose X kindly review or rate us on the App Store that really helps!

Added a new Clone Stamp tool under Editor Brush. You can now show or hide a layer. Tap on a layer on the layer stack viewer to access this menu option. You can now Replace image but keep mask for a layer. This option is also under the layer stack view s layer menu. A new tool has been added in the Color Wheel panel to pick a color from the screen. If you like using Superimpose X kindly review or rate us on the App Store that really helps!
